parameters:
Would you like to watch the event? If you've done something
wrong, you have to apologize.
\nc<Member>Anyone want to go on dispatch to the security company?
\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>I'd like to pass. I had a terrible experience last time...

\nc<Member 2>Oh, right. I heard about what happened to Saki. That must
have been traumatic.

\nc<Saki>It really was tough...\bustMsgExp[1, 0]By the way, where is
Meary-senpai?
\nc<Saki>It's not like our company has any holidays anyway...

\nc<Member>Ah, if you're looking for Meary-senpai, she's gone to attend
to the executives and VIPs. She's a confirmed member for
that.

\nc<Member 3>It was supposed to be at the end of the year, but it seems a
bit early this time.

\nc<Member>Well... knowing them, it wouldn't be surprising if they
changed plans at any time.

\nc<Saki>(A lot of VIPs and executives... This doesn't seem like a
good event.)

\nc<Employee>Saki is still in her first year, so she probably won't be
called, but we might be later on.
\bustMsgExp[1, 1]\nc<Saki>So, about today's dispatch to the security company...
\nc<Member 3>It's decided then, Saki. Good luck! We'll do our best too...

\bustMsgExp[1, 2]\nc<Saki>(Ugh, I'd usually complain, but the mood isn't right today.
Maybe I should just go quietly...)
\nc<Member>I heard Meary-senpai spoke highly of you recently?

\nc<Saki>(Yes, well. They probably think of me as one of the
executive's women...)\bustMsgExp[1, 0]Understood. I'm off!
